title: For Sale/Trade:  WJ HAUCK Custom Single Shot Rifle .219
postcontent: *** There is a portfolio of about 30 photos for this rifle at the link provided at the end of the ad text. *** For sale or trade is a Wilbur J. Hauck Single Shot Rifle which is a custom build on a Swiss made single shot folding lever action. Mr. Hauck was a master gunsmith and machinist who lived in the Arlington, VT area and built custom rifles starting in the 1940's. In the mid 1950's he patented a single shot action and produced a small number of rifles built on his action which are highly regarded by some collectors today. Information about Mr. Hauck and his rifles may be found on the internet. The rifle being offered for sale is not his patented action but appears to be a Swiss produced action and is different from a Martini action in that the lever hinge pin is forward of the triggers. The barrel is stamped ".219". This is either a 219 Zipper or an improved Zipper or a 219 Donaldson Wasp. There is no serial number. The rifle exhibits excellent craftsmanship and wood to metal fit is excellent. The rifle has double set triggers, Neidner style checkered steel butt plate, and a scalloped grip cap. The overall condition of the bluing is excellent and the wood shows a few very light handling marks. The barrel is 26" long, measures 1.085" at breech then tapers down to 0.780" at the muzzle. The screw heads are perfect showing absolutely no signs of ever having been turned. The rifle comes with a Fecker 12x scope and mounts. This scope is a high end scope from the 30's until the late 50's/early60's. The wood is a mid grade walnut in 90+% condition with a few light marks. Bluing on the gun itself is at 95% with some wear showing on the inside of the cocking lever and the bottom strap of the pistol grip. Blue on the scope is at 95% and it comes with the original screw in caps. CONDITIONS: Not for sale where prohibited by law. It is your responsibility to make sure you can legally own this where you reside. Will not sell/ship to NYC or surrounding counties. No sale or shipment to California. SHIPPING: I am not an FFL so I ship FFL to FFL only. A copy of an FFL is required and may be mailed with payment or emailed to me or my FFL. Shipping for this item is $75.00 which includes the cost of insurance. PAYMENT: USPS money order preferred but will gladly accept personal checks, non-USPS money orders, and bank checks. Payment by USPS money order will result in immediate shipment, other forms of payment will have to clear my account first. RETURNS: No return unless there is something wrong with the item that I did not see. No one is perfect and while I thoroughly check things out, it wouldn't be fair to arbitrarily hide behind a no return policy if there's something wrong that should have been noticed. QUESTIONS: Please email any questions you may have. *** ADDITIONAL PHOTOS LINK: https://photos.google.com/album/AF1QipN9-y8MSUmM8lzpygVMz0WDWZbu4TXyCmoySGCr
